    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/444.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cruisers <hi rend="italic">North Carolina</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington</hi> left on the 8th instant at midnight. I am informed by the
                    minister for foreign affairs that Morales has made a landing and is in hiding in
                    the neighborhood of Pedro Macoris and that yesterday an expedition under
                    Desiderio Arias left Nipe, Cuba, presumably for Monte Christi. The gunboat <hi
                        rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> is here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
